(53, 'SPECIALTY NURSING IN HOSPITALS ON DEMAND', 'specialty-nursing-in-hospitals-on-demand', '5aa2628e48a47.jpg', '2018-03-21', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Being a nurse isn’t an\r\neasy job – it involves a lot of compassion, sincerity, hard work and an acute\r\nsense of responsibility. If you’re someone who fits into these, then specialty\r\nnursing should be the option for you, especially so because it’s a rising\r\nprofession.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><o>&nbsp;</o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">If you\'re wondering\r\nwhat exactly nurses are supposed to do, here are some of the responsibilities:<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Preparing\r\na case study in the patient and examining his health conditions.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Managing\r\nthe wounds and other medical interventions.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Understanding\r\nthe patient condition and working out a plan to treat him.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Supervision\r\nof the patients.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Administering\r\ndrugs and other medical implements.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Carry\r\nout researches to make progress in the healthcare system.<o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><o>&nbsp;</o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Specialized nurses may\r\nbe of certain kinds depending on the degree or matter of specialization. Fret\r\nnot, here is a list of specialization offered at UHC Staffing:</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><o><br></o></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\"><o><br></o></span></p><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>Ambulatory Care Nurse<br></td><td>AIDS Care Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Cardiac Nurse<br></td><td>Rehabilitation Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Case Management Nurse<br></td><td>Correctional Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Enterosomal Therapy Nurse<br></td><td>Gastroenterology Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Endoscopic Nurse<br></td><td>Genetic Treatment Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Infection Control Nurse<br></td><td>Intravenous Therapy Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Managed Care Nurse<br></td><td>Long Term Care Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Nephrology Nurse<br></td><td>Neuroscience Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Occupational Nurse<br></td><td>Ophthalmic Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Oncology Nurse<br></td><td>Perioperative Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Orthopaedic Nurse<br></td><td>Otorhinolaryngology Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Pediatric Nurse<br></td><td>Prenatal Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Psychiatric Nurse<br></td><td>Primary Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Respiratory Nurse<br></td><td>School Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Transplant Nurse<br></td><td>Trauma Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Operating Room Nurse<br></td><td>Labor and Delivery Nurse<br></td></tr><tr><td>Utilization Review Nurse<br></td><td>Emergency Room Nurse<br></td></tr></tbody></table><p class=\"MsoNormalCxSpMiddle\" xss=\"removed\">Such specialization\r\nwill enable you to get jobs and recruitment in specialized positions in nursing\r\nhomes and hospitals with good payment<br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">Clinical nurse\r\nspecialists or CNS are generally employed in hospitals, nursing homes and\r\nclinics. If you hence specialize in any such department, you will be able to\r\nhandle a wide range of not only physical but also mental problems. As\r\nhealthcare is turning more specific with the advancement of technology to cater\r\nto all needs a patient might have, specialized personnel are desired in every\r\nfield. <o></o></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=\"removed\"><span xss=\"removed\">ualified nurses are\r\nnothing less than a boon to the civilization and <b>UHC Staffing</b> recognizes the same and brings to you excellent nurses\r\nwho are best at what they do.<o></o></span></p>', 'Nursing jobs, hospital nurse jobs,Specialty jobs', 'SPECIALTY NURSING IN HOSPITALS ON DEMAND', 'UHC Staffing provides information about; WHY SPECIALTY NURSING IN HOSPITALS ON DEMAND', 'SPECIALTY NURSING IN HOSPITALS', 1),
(58, 'NURSING SCHOOLS IN USA', 'nursing-schools-in-usa', '5b7fa7ca597cd.jpg', '2018-04-05', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Qualified nurses are in very high demand with the\r\nageing population across the United States of America. Apart from the medical\r\nassistance, they are essential for the leadership roles, education and\r\nadvocacy. With the rapid growth of baby boomers and increase in patients,\r\ncompanionate and savvy nurses have an excellent\r\nprospect of career advancement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The <b>University\r\nof Illinois</b> at Chicago is ranked first at the list of top ten nursing\r\nschools in America by the Global Network of WHO Collaborating Centres (WHOCCs). Students regardless of their\r\nbackground and race are taught about nursing by award-winning professors and\r\nclinicians there. Students gather knowledge about the medical industry in there\r\nthat helps in the betterment of patients’ lives domestic and abroad.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">There are numerous other nursing schools as well as in the United States of America, which\r\nare renowned for their curriculum and academic structure in the healthcare\r\nspectrum.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">University of Pennsylvania-</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> The Penn School of Nursing is most well known for their exclusive\r\nscholarships that help students from international shores to learn about\r\nnursing from astute technical faculties.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">UCLA-</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">the University\r\nof California-Los Angeles is one of the elite nursing institutions on the land\r\nof America. Their faculty includes noble laureates and multiple national\r\nacademy members.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">University of Alabama-</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> The University of Alabama is hugely\r\nrenowned for their campus diversity in culture, academics and economy. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Columbia University-</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Columbia School of Nursing,<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>is globally recognised\r\nas path-breaking contributors to the research and development of nursing. They\r\nhave made excellent progress in their curricular advancements.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">University of Michigan-</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"> The University of Michigan School of\r\nNursing (UMSN) lead the group of nursing institutions in America that welcome\r\nstudents from all around the globe. They have an exclusive program that allows\r\nstudents, researchers and teachers to join their nursing community.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Nursing duties mostly\r\nvary on the individual’s education and experience in the field. There also a\r\nfew factors that determine the cost of attending a medical nursing school in\r\nthe United States of America. One of the prime factors is the type of degree one individual is aiming to pursue in the\r\nfield. Different degree charges different tuition fees. With the several ways\r\nto become a nurse like bachelor’s degrees Licenced Practical Nurse (LPN),\r\nLicensed Vocational Nurse (LVN) and bridge programs from LPN or LVN. Bachelor’s\r\ndegrees usually cover four years to complete with $50,000 to $100,000 as\r\ntuition money in various private schools.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">It is essential to kick-start\r\na nursing career as soon as possible. The purpose of early beginning in a\r\nnursing career can be satisfied with associate degrees which take two years for\r\ncompetition. There are provisions for applying associate degree in LPN and LVN\r\nprograms as well. Each of these programs takes less than eighteen months to\r\nfinish which is comparatively much lesser than the bachelor’s programs. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Miscellaneous expenses like accommodation and health\r\ninsurances are also inclusive of the college budget which may vary from school\r\nto school. Studying nursing costs a large\r\nchunk of money every year, figuratively $1000 to $3000 for textbooks. Education\r\nin medicine also demands its students to bear the cost of attaining technical\r\ngadgets like stethoscopes, blood pressure apparatus, thermometers and much\r\nmore. The combined charge for all the devices just mentioned ranges up to $500.\r\nFigures like these inevitably seem to deluge. Hence there are a few options that\r\ncan benefit aspirants to reduce the overall expenditure. They must start by\r\napplying for Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) which offers\r\ndiscounts, grants and loans for educational\r\nprograms. The student loan route remains an alternative option as well.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'NURSING SCHOOLS IN USA', 'NURSING SCHOOLS IN USA', 'UHC Staffing provides information about the best nursing schools in USA.', 'NURSING SCHOOLS IN USA', 1),
(59, 'MEDICARE COSTS KEEPS RISING EVERY YEAR', 'medicare-costs-keeps-rising-every-year', '5b7fa8c1dfb83.PNG', '2018-04-16', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">According to U.S.\r\nGovernment healthcare agencies, the average medical expense is set to rise by\r\nat least 5.3% in the next year. The steep incline will continue to grow in the following decade. The primary reasons for\r\nthis growth include the growing population of the country that needs more and more medical attention each day,\r\nan increase in the prices of medical\r\ngoods and services. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The U.S. Centres for\r\nMedicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) predicted that healthcare costs would rise at a rapid rate of 5.5% in between\r\n2017 and 2026. The growing medical expenses will cover an anticipated average\r\nof 19.7% of the country’s economy by the year 2026, which would be a giant leap from 17.9% presently. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The fastest annual\r\ngrowth will be seen in prescription drugs\r\nby the next decade. With an average rate of 6.3%,\r\nprescription drugs that are used for a genetic disorder and cancer treatment will be\r\nresponsible for the rapid rise.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Government health\r\ninsurance programs will also contribute heavily due to the high spending in\r\nMedicare and Medicaid for the poor and disabled. The growing population are\r\nmore and more likely to rely on these healthcare services for aid.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The report also shares\r\nthat there will be more uninsured people in the country by 2026. The average\r\nrate of insured people will drop from 91.1% to 89.3% post the Republicans\r\noverturned the Obamacare’s mandate, which sees every person to buy health\r\ninsurance or pay fine.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Somefundamental</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> reforms\r\nmust be adapted to make sure Medicare is on a secured financial footing. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\nSymbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Create\r\na temporary Medicare Part A premium to avoid the HI trust deficit funds in the\r\nnext few years. The bonus will be terminated once the HI deficit fund is reduced\r\nand ignored.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\nSymbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Medicare\r\nPart B and Part D premiums will be steadily raised from 25% to 35% in the\r\nbeneficiary’s contribution. With 2% points per year, this process can be executed over the next five years.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\nSymbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Restrain\r\nthe current income limits, put them to inflation, and terminate the tax-payer\r\nsubsidies for the affluent retirees,\r\nwhich is 3% of the whole Medicare population.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\nSymbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-no-proof:yes\">The total</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">\r\ncost of each Medicare home wealth visit will have an addition of 10% co-payment.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Health saving accounts or HSAs, work in perfect\r\nalignment with highly deductible insurance options. Due to their tax-free\r\ndevelopment investors can make tax-free withdrawals, only if they are using the\r\nfinance for eligible medical expenses.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The high-income retirees will be compelled more than\r\never to spend a big chunk of money for\r\nthe coverage of their Medicare premiums. Going by the reports from the\r\nHealthView Services, an average 55-year old couple that earns $140,000 together\r\nare anticipating seeing their Medicare charges spike up to $122,000\r\nindividually. Due to the variation in how the healthcare program is charging\r\nits beneficiaries, the future retirees <a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>fear a much worse\r\nbite than their preliminary estimation.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'MEDICARE COSTS', 'MEDICARE COSTS KEEPS RISING EVERY YEAR', 'Find detailed information about; WHY MEDICARE COSTS KEEPS RISING EVERY YEAR.', 'MEDICARE COSTS', 1),
(60, 'MERGERS AND ACQUISITION IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING', 'mergers-and-acquisition-in-healthcare-staffing', '5b7fa9693e680.jpg', '2018-04-25', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Harvard Business\r\nReview reported that global mergers and acquisitions (M&amp;A) achieved a new\r\nmilestone in 2017 when more than 50,000\r\ndeals were completed for the third time\r\nin a row. The healthcare sector will see massive\r\ngrowth in the staffing industry by the next two years with M&amp;A activities\r\nas companies are looking to maximise on\r\ntheir value propositions. According to the U.S. Healthcare Staffing Market\r\nAssessment, the staffing industry is set to see a combined growth of 11% by the\r\nnext two years. Healthcare staffing M&amp;A will continue to see this growth\r\nthroughout 2018. Right at the beginning of the year, Medical Solutions who hold\r\nsignificant shares in the US market announced their plans to take over PPR. PPR\r\nis very well known for their travel nurse staffing and temporary leadership for\r\nacute and post-acute facilities. According to the press source, they will\r\ncontinue to run under the branding of PPR and practice from their two offices\r\nin Jacksonville and Tampa, Florida. It is important\r\nto mention that last year PPR acquired fellow travel nurse staffing\r\ncompany 360 Healthcare Staffing.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Several significant\r\ndeals followed suit the trend last year. We saw Cross Country Healthcare take\r\nover the assets of Advantage RN whereas Travel Nurse Across America (TNAA)\r\ntrumped over their competitor Trinity Healthcare Staffing Group (TSHG). By the TNAA/ TSHG, the acquirer took a giant\r\nleap from being eleventh to fifth in the top list of largest staffing companies\r\nin America.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The healthcare\r\nstaffing found its feet in the country with the 2010 Affordable Care Act (ACA)\r\nleading to the surge of new insured people, thereby increasing the patient\r\nnumbers in hospitals and nursing homes. The slowwave\r\nin the increase of insured people sky-rocketed\r\nthe demand for healthcare labour – even during the years when there was not\r\nmuch power in the U.S. economy. As the ACA is in effect, the growing population\r\nof the country has come forward with challenges to manage their healthcare.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">There are potential\r\nuncertainties as well, regarding the existence of the ACA in the future of the\r\nhealthcare staffing industry. The staffing of new registered nurses continues\r\nto remain a challenge for the firms, regardless of more nursing graduates. New\r\nnurses lack experience in several key areas of their profession, thereby\r\ncompelling the firms to think about offering custom apprenticeship programs to\r\nthose nurses. By those programs, they may be able to learn about the niche from\r\nexperienced professionals nearby. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Healthcare\r\nstaffing market in the United States is expected to rise at a compound average\r\ngrowth rate (CAGR) of 13.70% by 2021. With this prediction at the front, several international healthcare\r\nstaffing companies are penetrating into the American market. Going by the Bureau of Labor and Statistics\r\n(BLS), ove<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>r 500,000 nurses will retire by the year 2021. This will create a massive void in the workforce\r\nof the sector, thereby presenting an enormous potential for the staffers to\r\nmaximise on it.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'ACQUISITION IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING, MERGERS IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING', 'MERGERS AND ACQUISITION IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING', 'Find information about MERGERS AND ACQUISITION IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING.', 'ACQUISITION IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING, MERGERS IN HEALTHCARE STAFFING', 1),
(61, 'HOW TO CHECK YOUR SOCIAL SECURITY RETIREMENT AMOUNT?', 'how-to-check-your-social-security-retirement-amount?', '5b87c7da38c11.jpg', '2018-05-14', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Social Security</span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"> is a U.S social insurance\r\nprogram run and monitored by the U.S federal government under the Social\r\nSecurity Administration for the disabled and retired citizens. It provides support\r\nto the people under a number of contingencies like medical care, maternity\r\nbenefit, survivors’ benefits, unemployment benefits, family benefits and\r\ndisability benefits. <b>Retirement Benefits</b>\r\nor Old Age Pensions are a part of the Social Security program that can be\r\nredeemed after survival beyond a prescribed or pre-determined age. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Who Can Avail the Retirement\r\nBenefits?<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Even\r\nthough the entire concept of benefits might seem simple and straightforward,\r\nthe reality isn’t so kind. There are certain parameters and pre-requisites that\r\nneed to be met and fulfilled before one can become eligible to apply for\r\nretirement pay-out.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">First and foremost, AGE. A social security member needs to be\r\nat least 61 years and 9 months old to be eligible for this benefit. Generally,\r\npeople avail their retirement benefits between the ages of 62 years and 70\r\nyears.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">An applicant must not be receiving any other benefits that\r\nfall under the insurance program, except Medicare. All the other welfare income\r\nto the Social Record should be stopped.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">Married Couples and those who fall under the criteria for\r\nSurvivors’ benefits are eligible to avail <b>retirement\r\nbenefits</b>. Spousal benefits may be availed at the age of 62 years, but if\r\none waits till complete retirement, as they can, later on, switch to their own\r\nwork record and avail the pension pay-out which will be higher as their date of\r\nclaim will be delayed.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Estimating the Retirement Pay-out\r\nAmount<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">The\r\nbenefit amount is never the same for anyone and even for the same person. The\r\nfull benefit amount is calculated based on inflation, employment conditions and\r\nthe individual’s best thirty-five years of earnings. The age of entitlement,\r\nthe actual age when a person goes into retirement determines the specific\r\namount credited on a monthly basis. To estimate your full monthly retirement\r\nbenefit, you can try using the </span><span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"https://www.ssa.gov/OACT/quickcalc/\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Social Security</span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"> calculator</span></a></span><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">. </span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">Try entering a number retirement dates into the calculator.\r\nThe date and year you plan to first claim the welfare have a significant impact\r\non the amount you receive. For example, if you claim the benefits at age 62,\r\nthe amount you receive will be almost 25-30 percent less if you apply at age 66\r\nand probably around 50 percent less at age 70; so plan accordingly. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">As\r\nthis benefit plan provides a monthly pay-out for those who are eligible, there\r\nis no minimum benefit amount assigned to an individual. </span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">You may also\r\nreceive an estimate of your retirement amount by contacting the local Social\r\nSecurity office or by calling the toll free number 1-800-772-1213 (TTY:\r\n1-800-325-0778). But, if you earn a variable income that changes yearly, then\r\nan accurate estimation of your welfare amount is not possible.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'SOCIAL SECURITY RETIREMENT AMOUNT', 'HOW TO CHECK YOUR SOCIAL SECURITY RETIREMENT AMOUNT?', 'UHC Staffing provides important details about; HOW TO CHECK YOUR SOCIAL SECURITY RETIREMENT AMOUNT?', 'SOCIAL SECURITY RETIREMENT AMOUNT', 1),
(64, 'H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR THERAPISTS (PT/OT/SLP) AND HOW TO APPLY', 'h1b-visa-requirements-for-therapists-(pt/ot/slp)-and-how-to-apply', '5b92246003c11.jpg', '2018-05-28', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR THERAPISTS\r\n(PT/OT/SLP) AND HOW TO APPLY</span></u></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">The H1B visa is a temporary professional worker visa,\r\navailable to those with a four- year bachelor’s degree from the United States\r\nof America or abroad seeking an exclusive occupation position with a United\r\nStates employer. The particular visa is valid for a maximum of six years which can also lead to permanent residency as\r\nwell. Several workers on this visa obtain permanent resident visas or the green\r\ncard during their initial stays in America. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Medical therapists like the physical therapists,\r\noccupational therapists and speech-language\r\npractitioners need to qualify specific standards to avail H1B visa and the\r\ngreen card.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">The Physical Therapists require a master’s degree in\r\nphysical therapy and at least work experience in the related field for a year\r\nor two. The applicant will need to successfully pass the National Physical\r\nTherapists Exam (NPTE) as well. They will also have to provide the visa screen\r\ncertificate.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Much like the Physical Therapists, the occupational\r\ntherapists are also expected to present their bachelor’s degree in occupational\r\ntherapy with at least a year or two experiences in the related field. They also\r\nneed to pass the National Board for Certification in Occupational Therapy-\r\nOccupational Therapy Registered (NBCOT-OTR) exam. Furthermore, they will need\r\nto present their visa screen certificate as well.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">The Physical Therapists will have their education\r\ncredentials evaluated by either the Foreign Credentialing Commission on\r\nPhysical Therapy (FCCPT) or the International Consultants of Delaware (ICD).\r\nThey will also need to show the TOR, diploma, course syllabus, course\r\ndescription from the university they graduated. They must also prove the PT licensing credentials from the\r\nlicensing board of their countries. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Similar to the Physical Therapists, the Occupational\r\ntherapists will have their educational credentials reviewed by either the\r\nNational Board for Certification of in Occupational Therapy (NBCOT) or the Commission on Graduates of Foreign\r\nNursing Schools (CGFNS). Post the evaluation and reviewed by either of the authorities, the documents will be re-evaluated by the New York State Education\r\nDepartment (NYSED).<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">The candidates will need to apply for registration from the\r\nNew York State Board for Physical Therapy and New York State Board for Occupational\r\nTherapy respectively. They must print form 1 “Application for First\r\nRegistration” for occupational therapy. The candidates must fill all the\r\ninformation that is necessary for the forms. The signature on form 1 has to be notarised by a notary person. Then the forms\r\nmust be mailed to the NYSED. The applicants must keep checking on the\r\napplication progress.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">For further information on migrating to USA or Canada\r\ncontact our immigration team by sending your resume to </span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"\"><a href=\"mailto:jobs@uhcstaffing.com\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\">jobs@uhcstaffing.com</span></a></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> with\r\ndetails of your credentials and pre-requisites done</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">. <span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">or visit us at </span></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"\"><a href=\"http://www.uhcstaffing.com/\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\">www.uhcstaffing.com</span></a></span></font></span><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n14.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'Jobs For Therapy,Job in USA,Visa for USA,H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS', 'H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR THERAPISTS (PT/OT/SLP) AND HOW TO APPLY', 'UHC Staffing provides details about H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR THERAPISTS (PT/OT/SLP) AND HOW TO APPLY.', 'H1B VISA REQUIREMENTS', 1);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`b_id`, `title`, `slug`, `img`, `date`, `description`, `tags`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `keywords`, `status`) VALUES
(65, 'NURSING IN GENERAL', 'nursing-in-general', '5b9226c21fb65.jpg', '2018-06-07', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">NURSING IN GENERAL<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">Nursing is a fantastic career choice given the present\r\nsituation in the healthcare industry across the globe. The growing demand for medical attention across countries like the\r\nUnited States and Canada has ensured a significant financial reward and upward\r\nmobility opportunities for graduates. Even\r\nthough the profession is globally\r\nconsidered as a financially rewarding occupation with infinite job\r\nprospects, the best attractive highlight is this profession will command high\r\ndemand in decades to come. Nursing also ranks as a top rated occupation in the\r\nannual Gallop poll. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">Going by the numbers from the United States Bureau of Labor\r\nStatistics, there will be a shortage in\r\nthe nursing profession by one million when we reach 2020.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">A career in the nursing profession offers excellent benefits, thereby helping you to\r\nadjust your professional conditions as per your lifestyle. Any and every corner\r\nof the world needs medical attention. Strengthening the fact that nurses have\r\njobs across any geographic location and sector. They\r\nalso have the luxury of choosing either full-time or part-time duty. The\r\nsituation is very adaptive to your\r\nlifestyle as well. Not many professions will let the employee pick their workdays and work shifts that range\r\nbetween four to twelve-hour duties. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Working as a nurse guarantees outstanding\r\ncareer mobilityin life.</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"> As\r\nthe nurses work in a wide variety of\r\nplaces, you can be on the front line in trauma\r\ncare; you can choose to engage in a public\r\nhealth setting. Nurse consultant is also a possibility in case the candidate\r\nhas an interest in the legal system.\r\nSimilar, if the interest lies in teaching, then you can also opt to be an\r\neducator and work with children. The opportunities for a nurse are unending in\r\nthe health industry.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">Unlike most other jobs, nursing guarantees no burnout in\r\nthe profession. The claim is established on a stronger foundation when you\r\nlearn from an active nurse that none of her days is similar and less-challenging. You will be always on your heels and learn to tackle\r\nchallenges. Nurses are mostly part of teams alongside health-care\r\nprofessionals. There are times when they are expected to step up and lead the\r\ncollective group of people in planning,\r\nimplementing and evaluating programs. The profession benefits individuals in\r\ndeveloping the trait to work collectively with people and perform leadership\r\nduties as well.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\">An under shadowing benefit of nursing is the profession\r\ndoes not care about the academic background of the aspirant. Employers only\r\nvalue the experience in the industry. In\r\ncase you have a degree, they will demand\r\nyou to join accelerated or post accelerated nursing programs. While they are\r\ntime-consuming, they help the students in developing exclusive in-depth\r\nknowledge. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">For further information on nursing jobs contact our recruitement\r\nteam by sending your resume to </span><span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"mailto:jobs@uhcstaffing.com\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\">jobs@uhcstaffing.com</span></a></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"> with\r\ndetails of your credentials. We will be able to assist you with your next\r\nnursing job <a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>or visit us at </span><span lang=\"EN-IN\"><a href=\"http://www.uhcstaffing.com/\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\">www.uhcstaffing.com</span></a></span></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'GENERAL NURSING JOBS, Jobs for nurse', 'Nursing Jobs in General', 'UHC Staffing provides the best Nursing Jobs in General. Visit our website for details about nursing jobs in general.', 'Nursing Jobs in General', 1),
(66, 'FOREIGN-TRAINED THERAPISTS IN USA AND CANADA', 'foreign-trained-therapists-in-usa-and-canada', '5b92384ac6063.jpg', '2018-06-20', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">Foreign-Trained\r\ntherapists in USA and Canada<o:p></o:p></font></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">Therapists\r\nare skilled personnel who have a specialisation in a particular kind of\r\ntherapy. Psychologists, Psychiatrists, Physio/Physical Therapists, Occupational\r\nTherapists, and counsellors can all be considered “Therapists”. &nbsp;Many such professionals are keen on pursuing\r\nor expanding their practices to countries like the USA and Canada where the\r\nopportunities are unlimited, and income can be better. After graduating from\r\nmed school with a license to practice, a therapist can either start his\r\nindependent practice or become associated with a medical or even defence\r\norganisation (military therapists, profilers,<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a> and\r\nanalysts).<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\"><b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">Foreign-trained therapists </span></b><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\">need to meet certain\r\nrequirements and clear a particular set of steps before they become eligible to\r\napply for and start work in USA and Canada. The rules and regulations of the\r\ntwo countries are different, and they accept the applications according to\r\ntheir standards.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><o:p><font face=\"Arial\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">CANADA<o:p></o:p></font></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">While\r\napplying for a work permit as a therapist, there are some organisations that\r\ndetermine the standards and provide guidelines. The Canadian Association of\r\nOccupational Therapists (CAOT), Canadian Psychology Association (CPA) and the\r\nCanadian Alliance of Physiotherapy Regulators (CARP) are the significant\r\norganisations handling the licensure of therapists in Canada. The guidelines\r\nand pre-requisites to be accepted as a therapist vary according to the kind of\r\ntherapy, but most of these instructions bear similarities.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">One must determine the province or territory they want to\r\npractice in. Most provinces and territories have independent organisations that\r\nmonitor various therapy professions in their region and are responsible for\r\ngranting licences to the foreign-trained professionals. Each regulatory\r\nassociation has its own requirements, and the applicant should contact the one\r\nin the desired province or territory to clarify doubts and avoid confusion.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">The credentialing process can be started when you are in your\r\nhome country. Once the credentials are assessed, you can apply to be registered\r\naccording to the province and receive a licence to practice. A regulatory\r\norganisation will grant you eligibility to appear for a certification or\r\ncompetency examination. Passing this exam is mandatory for all applicants.</span></font><span style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><u><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">USA<o:p></o:p></font></span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">The\r\nwork application process for foreign-educated professionals in the USA is\r\ngoverned by U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS).&nbsp; The physical therapy regime is governed by\r\nthe Federation of State Boards of Physical Therapy (FSBPT). In congregation\r\nwith USCIS, FSBPT also works with the Foreign Credentialing Commission on\r\nPhysical Therapy (FCCPT) and the Commission on Graduates of Foreign Nursing\r\nSchools (CGFNS) to handle applications. The credentials of the applicant are\r\nput under scrutiny during the review. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">The\r\nreview comprises of:<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">Educational Credentials Review (all educational documents are\r\nevaluated).<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">Eligibility verification<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">English Proficiency Verification. <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">VISA Screening.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 107%; color: rgb(2, 6, 33); letter-spacing: 0.25pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">After this process, the FCCPT will issue\r\na Health Care Worker Certificate, (Type I).</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"> Once the credentials are approved,\r\nand all required documentation has been provided, the jurisdiction determines\r\nwhether the applicant is required to take the MCQ based National Physical\r\nTherapy Exam (NPTE), a licensure exam. The fees for this exam are US$370.00 for\r\nboth Physical Therapist and Physical Therapy Assistant. Successful completion\r\nof this exam will be rewarded with a licence to practice as a Physical Therapist\r\nor Physical Therapy Assistant in that jurisdiction only. It is important that\r\nyou contact the licensing authority of the state where you wish to apply for\r\nlicensure before submitting your credentials for evaluation. <o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><o:p><font face=\"Arial\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%\"><font face=\"Arial\">Foreign-train\r\ntherapists have a wide scope and tremendous opportunities in the USA and\r\nCanada. The application processes and eligibility criteria are straightforward\r\nand easy to understand. Even though work experience is not required to apply\r\nfor licensure in either country, having an experience of one or two years under\r\nbelt will undoubtedly bolster your resume and make it more appealing.</font></span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'THERAPISTS IN USA, THERAPISTS IN CANADA', 'FOREIGN-TRAINED THERAPISTS IN USA AND CANADA		', 'UHC Staffing provides the best job opportunities to foreign-trained therapists in USA and Canada. Visit our website for for more detailed information about healthcare jobs.', 'THERAPISTS IN USA, THERAPISTS IN CANADA', 1),
(67, 'WHAT IS HIPAA COMPLIANCE IN HEALTHCARE', 'what-is-hipaa-compliance-in-healthcare', '5b923f7148d21.jpg', '2018-06-30', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"line-height: 115%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><b>WHAT IS HIPAA COMPLIANCE IN HEALTHCARE</b></span><br></span></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">The Health Insurance Portability and\r\nAccountability Act (HIPAA</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">)\r\nworks as a standard for the protection of delicate patient data. Protected\r\nhealth information (PHI) should have a network,\r\nprocess and physical measures in place for the companies that deal with and follow them to ensure secure\r\nHIPAA compliance. Covered entities (CE) are also\r\nincluded; people who offer treatment,\r\npayment and operations in healthcare, business associates, people with access\r\nto patient information and provide support in ailment, fees or services.&nbsp; Subcontractors and business associates of\r\nbusiness associates should also comply.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">The U.S. Department of Health and Human\r\nServices (HHS</span><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">) says that the HIPAA\r\nPrivacy Rule or the standards for privacy of individually identifiable health\r\ninformation demands exceptional standards\r\nfor the protection of specific health information. Furthermore, the rule sets a\r\nnew set of security standards for protecting particular\r\nmedical information, which is stored in the\r\nelectronic medium. The Security Rule also\r\noperationalises the privacy rule’s protection by treating both the technical\r\nand non-technical safeguards that covered entities should be put in the right place to ensure individuals’\r\nelectronic PHI (e-PHI). In between HHS, the\r\nOffice of Civil Rights (OCR) is creditworthy for imposing the Privacy and Security Rules with voluntary\r\ncompliance activities and civil money penalties.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">The HHS demands physical and technical safeguards for\r\norganisations holding sensitive patient data. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Physical safeguards include-<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Authorised\r\naccess can only control and access the limited facility<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Policies\r\nabout implementation and access to workstations and electronic media<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Limitations\r\nfor sharing, erasing, disposing and recycling electronic press and ePHI<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Technical safeguards include-<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l1 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Using\r\ncustomised user IDs, emergency access procedures, automatic log off, both\r\nencryption and decryption<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;\r\nmso-list:l1 level1 lfo2\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><font face=\"Arial\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\">Audit\r\nreports on tacking logs that record activity on both hardware and software<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">An auxiliary act was passed\r\nin 2009 known as The Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical\r\nHealth (HITECH) Act that affirms by the enforcement of HIPAA requirements\r\nthrough the penalties of health organisations that desecrate HIPAA Privacy and\r\nSecurity Rules. The Act was forged as a\r\nresponse to health technology development and enhanced implementation, storage\r\nand transmittal of electronic health information. <o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;\"><font face=\"Arial\">Compliance with the Health Insurance Portability and\r\nAccountability Act (HIPAA) is considered\r\nas a pivotal part for people who are responsible for health information. The ultimate data protection solutions\r\nidentify and protect patient data across all forms, including structured and\r\nunstructured data, emails, documents, and scans, while letting healthcare\r\nproviders share data securely guarantee the best <a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>comprehensive patient care.&nbsp;</font><font face=\"Garamond, serif\"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>', 'HIPAA COMPLIANCE', 'WHAT IS HIPAA COMPLIANCE IN HEALTHCARE', 'UHC Staffing provides information about HIPAA, which helps to practitioners comply with the requirements of the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act.', 'HIPAA COMPLIANCE', 1),
(68, 'TRAVEL NURSING IS NOT FOR EVERYBODY', 'travel-nursing-is-not-for-everybody', '5bec0aa59578f.jpg', '2018-07-06', '<p>Even though travel nursing is one of the most promising and rewarding careers in the healthcare industry, things are not always hunky–dory all the times. The profession also comes with its share of challenges for individuals who want to get involved in the business. Much like all other jobs in the world, this profession also has several pitfalls. However, one must know the right way to tackle those to reach the very top of success in their career in the healthcare industry. Let’s talk about a few challenges that are frequent in the work of travel nursing and why it is not considered viable for absolutely everybody or anybody.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1) Family issues: The most exciting aspect of travel nursing can very well be the worse aspect of travel nursing. The professionals are expected to work on different shores and lands, staying miles away from their family and friends. Many individuals find it\r\nincredibly hard to tackle loneliness during the initial days of the contract. The right solution to this issue is to establish new contacts or make new friends. Although the process does not bear fruit immediately, it turns out to be a handy alternative eventually.</p>\r\n<p>2. Sudden home-calls: Travel nurses are always on the road to reach every corner of the country that needs medical attention. While they are under contract and working in some\r\nmedical institution, situations may arise when they might have to return home on a temporary or a permanent basis. A crisis like somebody’s death, personal health issues and a few more, genuinely demand the individual’s presence back in his or her family.\r\nDuring this time, the nurse must decide to inform both the staffing agency and the medical institution. Altering the staffing agency first will give them a shot at filling the soon-to-be vacant position with another nurse or strike up a negotiation with the\r\nhospital for the nurse’s best interest.</p>\r\n<p>3. Abnormal work routines: Travel nurses are mostly required by medical institutions and hospitals that are running short on staffs. The professionals are used to fill the void, and may necessarily have short stints with the respective medial institutions. As hospitals are forever working to aid patients, nurses are mostly prepared to work through different work routines. Although things often turn tough for travel nurses who may have to work during abnormal work hours like night duty or long extensive hours. The key to finding happiness in the experience is to realise the nobility of the job and the fact that they are serving the community.</p>\r\n<p>4. Quick learning: Quick learning is one of the most decorated skillsets a nurse can have in the healthcare industry. Most travel nurses have this in their repertoire as they are always changing workstations and colleagues. They need to adapt immediately to new work environments and personnel to perform their duties. Being able to learn things quickly benefits them by incorporating new techniques and ideas from unknown places.</p><p><br></p><p>More Information please visit our website :- <a href=\"http://www.uhcstaffing.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.uhcstaffing.com</a></p>', 'Travel Nursing Jobs', 'TRAVEL NURSING IS NOT FOR EVERYBODY', 'UHC Staffing provides important details why travel nursing jobs are not for everybody. Visit our website and get complete information about travel nursing.', 'Travel Nursing Jobs', 1),
(69, 'WHY NEW GRAD NURSES ARE NOT GETTING HIRED', 'why-new-grad-nurses-are-not-getting-hired', '5bec0c7138254.jpg', '2018-07-17', '<p>Ever since the recession hit the prosperous land of the United States of America, the healthcare industry has been the only most significant sector for job growth. However, the fact does not inherently mean that getting employed in the industry is very easy. Registered nurses that are fresh graduates are finding it extremely tough to negotiate with the market. More and more employers are dismissing new graduates right, left and centre as they are only interested in hiring experienced nurses. The National Student Nurse’s Associations have stated that about 36% of newly licensed Registered Nurses graduating in 2011 were unemployed till four months post their graduation. In Central California, the problem looks even worse with 43% RNs not having any job within the first eighteen months of their graduation. Such facts were extracted from a 2011 survey that was conducted by the California Institute of Nursing &amp;amp; Healthcare (CINHC).</p><p>The situation is not at all inspiring with all the employers only seeking experienced professional for their vacancies, yet they are adamant about hiring fresh recruits. About 90% of nurses are women of which 60% are married and a quarter is above the exclusive age bracket of 50. It is sufficiently rational for nurses to take a break in their thirties to raise their kids. Due to the long shifts on toes, most nurses retire in their late fifties. A significant statistic says that before the recession in the United States; about 73,000 nurses left the workforce each year due to multiple reasons like childbearing, retirement, burning out or death. </p><p>Simultaneously, nursing colleges recorded increasing growth in enrolment. The American Association of Colleges of Nursing has shared that more than 170,000 people enrolled through entry-level baccalaureate nursing programs in 2010-11. The number is staggeringly double the students from a decade earlier.</p><p>The high demand for healthcare services will only rise in the charts as more and more baby</p><p>boomers progress to their retiring stage in life. The application will be encouraged as healthcare reforms continue to make medical attention accessible to everyone. Healthcare administrators need to structure long-range plans and improvements for offering expert nurses at the bedside in the oncoming future. The novice nurses must be prepared to step in when the current staff moves on to their retirement. New nurse orientation programs must be installed for the fresh grads to learn the nuances of the business before joining duty.</p><p><br></p><p>More information please visit our website : - www.uhcstaffing.com</p>', 'NEW GRAD NURSES', 'WHY NEW GRAD NURSES ARE NOT GETTING HIRED', 'UHC Staffing has listed some basic reasons, why new grad nurses are not getting hired in hospitals and medical colleges.', 'NEW GRAD NURSES, Hire Grad Nuses', 1),
(70, 'SAFETY TIPS FOR EXERCISING IN THE HEAT', 'safety-tips-for-exercising-in-the-heat', '5bec0f6c15649.jpg', '2018-07-30', '<p>The summers are near and all of us want to exercise outdoors. Exercising outdoors is not only beautiful but also has other major perks. If you do not stay at a place that is naturally hot, you\r\ncan use this opportunity to travel somewhere new and exciting, all the while exploring new places and destinations.<br></p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you have already decided that you will exercise outside in the heat, like cycling on a warm sunny day, there are certain things that you need to keep in mind. Safety should be your first and major concern and therefore in today’s article we will discuss some important safety tips to follow while exercising in the heat. <br>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n1. Exercise Early\r\nAs children we were always taught that waking up early and making it a way of life will lead us\r\nto great benefits in the future. The same principle applies to exercising as well. Therefore you\r\nshould strictly avoid exercising when the majority of the sun is out. For example, don’t exercise\r\nin between 10 am to 3 pm, as this is usually the hottest time of the day. Exercising early will not\r\nkeep your body cool, you will feel more relaxed and calm after the exercise because of the cool\r\nweather outside.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n2. Light Colours\r\nWe have all seen the commercials of popular sports brands like Nike and Adidas. When they are\r\npromoting their outdoor exercise sportswear, look closely and you will find several light\r\ncolours. Wearing light colours when exercising outdoors will ensure that your clothes will\r\nreflect the heat from the sun thus cooling down your body faster.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Another aspect to remember is to wear loose fitting clothes. This will allow a much greater\r\ndegree of air circulation in your body thus ensuring that your sweat dries up fast and you are\r\ncool by the end of your exercise session.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n3. Sunscreen\r\nWhen we think about exercising, we are all pumped up and easily forget about our health. In\r\nthis case we forget that exercising outside without proper protection of our skin might have\r\ndevastating effects. Thus before going for your run or cycling, make it a point to apply\r\nconsiderable sunscreen on your exposed skin.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nWell Hydrated\r\nThis is one of the most common tips in the entire list, and still a lot of us tend to ignore this fact.\r\nWhile exercising your body will sweat a lot. This means that you will quickly loose energy if you\r\ndon’t end up hydrating your body at regular intervals during your workout.<br>\r\nMake sure to carry a bottle of cool water at all times during your outdoor exercise. Whenever\r\nyou feel drained out and tired, take a sip of it and your energy will quickly replenish.\r\nConclusion<br>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLike most other things in life, outdoor exercise too comes with a lot of advantages and\r\ndisadvantages. While the disadvantages are clearly lower, follow the above list of safety tips in\r\norder to avoid them completely.\r\n</p>', 'healthcare california,Health care Agency in california ', 'SAFETY TIPS FOR EXERCISING IN THE HEAT IN UHC STAFFING', 'FIND SAFETY TIPS FOR EXERCISING IN THE HEAT AT UHC STAFFING.', 'SAFETY TIPS FOR EXERCISING IN THE HEAT, Health care Agency in california, Health Care stafing servises', 1),
(78, 'DIABETES AND HOW TO HELP KIDS THAT ARE PRE-DIABETIC', 'diabetes-and-how-to-help-kids-that-are-pre-diabetic', '5bf3a423572e6.jpg', '2018-08-10', '<p>If you are a parent of a pre diabetic child, you are well aware of the challenges that comes in daily life. Especially with food, there a lot of challenges and often times you get confused as to what you should feed your child. On top of that, being pre diabetic means that the doctor or physician supervising your child’s health has fixed a chart which outlines the amount of food,the timings for the same and suggested quantity. From time to time, it becomes difficult for both the parent and the child to keep up with this chart and they are more than willing to take cheat days. But in those days too, there are only specific healthy foods that your child can have.</p><p>As a parent, you might confused as to what your child needs to eat and what is actually healthy for him or her. Therefore to help you out, we have coagulated a list of 9 ways, following which you can make sure your child is always eating healthy.</p><ol><li>We all know that vegetables and fruits are very healthy for humans no matter at what age they are. Therefore continuing this tradition give your child one fruit or one vegetable during every snack and meal.</li><li>If your child is a fan of your spaghetti sauce, introduce chopped vegetables in it as well.A good choice for vegetables can be frozen chopped spinach, or broccoli. After you have simmered the mixture for a while, put the entire thing in a food processor and no will ever come of the actual ingredients you used to make this yummy sauce.</li><li>You can follow the same style of adding vegetables when you are cooking your kid’s favorite macaroni as well. Additionally start introducing your child to whole-wheat pasta. The sooner they are exposed to it, the more easily they will accept it.</li><li>When preparing sandwiches and other delicacies which involves the use of butter or cheese, try avoiding them. Instead go for a seasoning of healthy olive oil.</li><li>Most kids these days love French fries. But instead of the store ones that are just ready to cook and are extremely unhealthy settle them for oven baked ones. While making them use a little bit of olive oil and bake for 50 minutes or until they are tender. During serving, sprinkle a little bit of salt on top and serve with ketchup.</li><li>One of the best ways to make your kids at healthy is to include them in the cooking process. Historically it has been proved that kids love eating what they have cooked. Therefore the chances of them enjoying their self-cooked healthy meals are higher.</li><li>Last but not the least, is setting up an example for your children. Always remember that kids develop habits and grow up to become what they see on a daily basis. Likewise if you want them to eat healthy and stay fit, make sure you follow the same routine and pattern.</li></ol><p>All the best!</p><p>United Health care staffing is a medical staffing and managed services provider in healthcare. Visit us at www.uhcstaffing.com</p>', 'diabetic child ', 'DIABETES AND HOW TO HELP KIDS THAT ARE PRE-DIABETIC', 'Prediabetes is defined by plasma glucose levels that are elevated above the normal range, but below the threshold for diabetes.', 'DIABETES, KIDS WITH PRE-DIABETIC, ', 1),
(79, 'NEW HEALTHCARE INITIATIVES BY SILICON VALLEY', 'new-healthcare-initiatives-by-silicon-valley', '5bf3ac1507abe.jpg', '2018-08-21', '<div>Recently tech giant Apple announced the launch of its own health clinics, where employees can get a checkup done at substantially low costs. With this move it is evidently clear that these companies are taking an active initiative to care for the health of their employees better.</div><div><br></div><div><div>This new shift in perspective comes as a result of the rising cost of healthcare in the United States. Therefore major companies like Apple are making attempts to try and improve the quality of healthcare all their employees receive. One of the most prominent ways to make this&nbsp; happen is to start building exclusive health clinics with access only to employees of the organization. These clinics are typically located near the company headquarters and have traditionally proved to be helpful to the employees of many organizations like banks and hospitals.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Apple is the latest addition to the list of organizations hosting such clinics. Apple is calling its clinic network AC Wellness Networks and has said in a press release that this clinic will run independently from the organization and its employees are the only ones who can get treated here.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Other than this, Apple is also financing several research programs like the Apple Heart Study which uses an app on the Apple Watch to track and analyze the heart of the wearer.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Other tech giants like Google and Microsoft are also accelerating their efforts to remake</div><div>healthcare by either developing or collaborating with other organizations to make tools for doctors, medical institutions and of course patients. In 2017 alone, the 10 largest tech companies in the United States of America were involved in healthcare deals, which has a net worth of more than 2.7 billion United States dollars. Previous to this, the figure was only around 277 million Unites States Dollars in 2012, and therefore it can be clearly seen that the efforts have been accelerated at quiet a fast pace.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Each tech company in the world is trying to make an impact in the healthcare industry by focusing on its core strengths and offerings. At the beginning of this article, we quoted the example of Apple, while Microsoft is focusing its efforts on online storage and analytics service while Google is more focused towards data that bring about actionable insights in the near future.</div><div><br></div><div><div>To conclude, it can be safely said that there is no one tech company that is invested in this business. While some are approaching this as a great business initiative, others are more focused towards portraying themselves as rescuers among the masses.</div><div><br></div><div><div>United Health care staffing is a medical staffing and managed services provider in healthcare. Visit us at www.uhcstaffing.com</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>', 'Healthcare Initiatives ', 'New Healthcare Initiatives By Silicon Valley', 'UHC Staffing provides information about NEW HEALTHCARE INITIATIVES BY SILICON VALLEY.', 'HEALTHCARE INITIATIVES BY SILICON VALLEY', 1),
(80, 'ABA THERAPY FOR CHILDREN', 'aba-therapy-for-children', '5bf3ade2ac734.jpg', '2018-08-29', '<div>Each year thousands of children from across the globe suffer from autism. A study conducted by CDC or the Centre for Disease Control and Prevention showed that every year 1 in 59 children are born with Autism. Looking at these statistics, it is fairly clear that autism is a much popular disease than it was a couple of years ago. But the question remains, what are the ways to treat autism?</div><div><br></div><div><div>Experts and physicians from around the world have suggested that Applied Behaviour Analysis abbreviated as applied behaviour analysis can be one of the most effective treatments for patients diagnosed with autism.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What is applied behaviour analysis?</b></div><div><div>Although there are many forms of specific behavioural therapy available in the medical</div><div>industry, applied behaviour analysis is one of the most common behavioural techniques used by doctors and physicians on patients suffering from certain developmental disabilities like Autism.</div><div><br></div><div><div>This behavioural therapy was developed in the late 1960s and is categorized by a series of analysis and careful observation of challenging behaviour occurring in the natural environment of a child. After the observation and analysis is complete, the child undergoes a behaviour intervention plan in order to produce more natural and adaptive ways of responding to certain situations. Since its inception, the applied behaviour analysis procedure has been successfully used among a variety of children with problems of developmental nature as well as those with autism specific nature.</div><div><br></div><div><div>The best advantage of using the applied behaviour analysis procedure on children with</div><div>developmental disorders is the fact that it can be used to teach both basic skills such as listening, looking, and imitating and can also be used to teach complex skills such as</div><div>understanding perspectives, reading as well as conversing. In a number of cases, these</div><div>therapeutic techniques were also used to help children overcome challenges like change in schedule and changes in environment which were unexpected and sudden.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Unlike other therapeutic treatments where there is a specific guideline that needs to be</div><div>followed, in APPLIED BEHAVIOR ANALYSIS no such method is there. The basic concepts of the procedure is studied by the therapist or physician and then based on the child’s skills, level of functioning and abilities, they are tailored and changed to meet individual needs and expectations.</div><div><br></div><div><div>The underlying concept of applied behaviour analysis is to positively reinforce desire behaviour and ignore unwanted or undesired behaviour or patient.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Who can benefit the most from applied behaviour analysis?</b></div><div><div>Almost all children who have diagnosed with some kind of behaviour therapy may it be autism or something else can benefit from applied behaviour analysis or other similar developmental diseases. The main focus of a therapist while conducting applied behaviour analysis on a child is to teach new adaptive behaviours which will be beneficial to them in the long run.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Also in children who do not suffer from any particular development disease, applied behaviour analysis can be used to motivate them to reach certain therapeutic goals.</div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><br></div></div>', 'ABA THERAPY FOR CHILDREN,ABA THERAPY NURSING JOBS', 'ABA THERAPY FOR CHILDREN', 'UHC Staffing Blog includes most useful information related with ABA THERAPY FOR CHILDREN. For more details, visit our website uhcstaffing.com', 'ABA THERAPY', 1),
(83, ' HEALTHY EATING HABITS AND DIABETES', 'healthy-eating-habits-and-diabetes', '5bf6dca8cedad.jpg', '2018-09-05', '<div>In todays’ world diabetes is one of the most harmful diseases. In a recent study conducted by the Centre for Disease Control and Prevention, abbreviated as CDC, it was found that more than 9.4 per cent of the population of United States is diagnosed with diabetes of some kind or another. For those of you who don’t understand the gravity of 9.4 per cent of a country’s population, it translates to almost 30.3 million Americans. Therefore it can be safely said that diabetes is a growing concern and therefore must be controlled in some way or the other. But how?</div><div><br></div><div><div>Before we delve into the intricacies of how healthy eating habits can counter your diabetes, let us first understand the basics.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What is diabetes?</b></div><div><div>In layman terms, diabetes is defined as a disease in which the body’s ability to produce and respond to insulin is temporarily or permanently disabled. This results in abnormal metabolism and in most cases elevated levels of glucose in a patient’s blood.</div><div><br></div><div><b>What is a diabetes diet?</b></div><div><div style=\"\">A diabetes diet can be simply explained as eating healthy and nutritious choice of food in&nbsp;moderate and adequate amounts at particular times of the day. The underlying idea in a&nbsp;diabetes diet is rich in nutrients and low in fat and calories. The key elements of this diet are&nbsp;essentially fruits, whole grains and vegetables<b>.</b></div><div style=\"\"><b><br></b></div><div style=\"\"><b>What is the purpose of a diabetes diet?</b></div><div style=\"\"><div style=\"\">If you are someone who has been diagnosed with diabetes or pre diabetes, it is most likely that&nbsp;<div style=\"display: inline !important;\">your doctor or dietician will advise you to change to a healthy eating plan. The main purpose&nbsp;</div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\">behind shifting to a healthy eating plan is to control the amount of sugar in your blood, control&nbsp;</div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\">the risks of a heart disease and also counter weight gain, high blood fats and high blood sugar.</div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><br></div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><br></div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><b>What are the recommended foods in a diabetes diet?</b></div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><b><br></b></div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><div style=\"\">As mentioned above, the idea of a diabetes diet is to eat healthy and well balanced meal three&nbsp;<div style=\"display: inline !important;\">times a day at particular timings. The main constituents of a diabetes diet is nutrition and less in&nbsp;</div><div style=\"font-weight: bold; display: inline !important;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">fat and sugar. Mentioned below are the main pointers for the same</span>:</div><div style=\"font-weight: bold; display: inline !important;\"><br></div><div style=\"font-weight: bold; display: inline !important;\"><br></div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\"><ol><li>Carbohydrates: When you consume food, both the simple carbohydrate and complex carbohydrates are broken down into blood glucose in your body. Thus focusing on healthy carbohydrates from foods such fruits, whole grains and legumes will help a lot.</li><li>Fibers: If you are person who binges heavy on dietary fibers, then it is time to cut them down as your body can’t absorb them at all. Fiber is the main moderator of how your body digests and controls blood sugar, therefore focus on natural fiber reach foods like whole grain, nuts and legumes.</li><li>Fish: If you are someone who loves meat a lot, then it is time you shift to fish. Eating fish which is healthy for your heart two times a week will help in the long run.</li><li>Fats: Focus only on good fats like those obtained from pecans and walnuts. But don’t overdo this, as this too might add up soon.</li></ol><p>Conclusion</p><p>Countering diabetes is easier said than done. By following the above mentioned points you will be on the right track to slowly curb diabetes. All the best!</p></div></div><br></div></div><br></div><br></div></div></div>', ' HEALTHY EATING HABITS', ' HEALTHY EATING HABITS AND DIABETES', 'UHC Staffing Blog Provides useful information about HEALTHY EATING HABITS AND DIABETES. For more details, visit our website uhcstaffing.com', ' HEALTHY EATING HABITS, DIABETES', 1);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`b_id`, `title`, `slug`, `img`, `date`, `description`, `tags`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `keywords`, `status`) VALUES
(84, 'MEASURE WEIGHT LOSS - ART OF HEALING', 'measure-weight-loss-art-of-healing', '5bf3dd6f833bf.jpg', '2018-09-17', '<div>Most of us are hyped about losing weight. We try a variety of diets and health plans which lead us to ultimately loose the desired amount of weight. But often in most scenarios, we fall short of measuring how much weight we actually lost. We miss out on the point that weight loss is not about shedding those extra points and the weight scale going down significantly. It is much more than that and in today’s article we will discuss just that.</div><div><br></div><div><div>When it comes to weight loss, there are three simple measurements we need to keep in mind. First is of course our weight, second is our fat percentage and third is waist hip ratio.</div><div><br></div><div>I<b>deal BMI</b></div><div><div style=\"\">A persons BMI or Body Mass Index is a scale which is used by doctors and medical practioners&nbsp;around the world to understand how plump a person is. Depending on the score of their BMI,&nbsp;doctors can easily determine if the person is underweight, perfect, obese or over weight at any&nbsp;point in time. The current guideline that is followed across the world states that the average&nbsp;BMI of a male should be in the range of 18.5 to 24.9, which translates to a weight between 53.5&nbsp;to 72 kilo grams for males. The same calculation holds true for females as well.</div><div style=\"\"><br></div><div style=\"\"><b>Body fat percentage</b></div><div style=\"\"><div style=\"\">If you are a person who is slightly more concerned about their weight than your peers, you&nbsp;<div style=\"display: inline !important;\">should be aware of your body fat percentage as well. In layman terms, your body fat&nbsp;</div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\">percentage translates to how much of your weight is made up of fat and how much of muscles.&nbsp;</div><div style=\"display: inline !important;\">Most clinics now a days have weight machines which can easily count your body fat percentage.</div></div><div>The logic behind the importance of body fat percentage is that, excess fat which makes you overweight is highly unsuitable for your body. Not only does it make you lazy, excess fat in your body increases the risk of fatal diseases at a later point in life.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Hip Ratio</b></div><div><div style=\"\">Last but not the least, is your knowledge about waist hip ratio. In order to measure this, you need to calculate both your hip and waist size and then compare them with the ideal measurements in a chart. The score you get will help doctors and medical practioners understand where your excess fat is being stored.</div><div style=\"\"><div>A high score usually indicates that you have a lot of fat in the abdominal region which will severely increase your chances of a fatal disease later on.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Conclusion</b></div><div><div style=\"\">Now that you know what all measurements are needed before you move forward with weight loss, make sure to follow these rules to get the perfect measurement every time.</div><ol><li>Always use a non-stretchable measuring tape for taking all your measurements. This willgive you accurate results and is easy to operate as well.</li><li>During measurement always make sure that the measuring tape is leveled with your body and it is always parallel to the floor.</li><li>Last but not the least, try to keep the tape as close to your skin as possible,&nbsp; ithout depressing it.</li></ol><p>More information please visit our website :-&nbsp; www.uhcstaffing.com</p><p><br></p><br></div></div><br></div></div><br></div></div>', 'MEASURE WEIGHT LOSS', 'MEASURE WEIGHT LOSS - ART OF HEALING', 'Find detailed information about MEASURE WEIGHT LOSS Causes.', 'MEASURE WEIGHT LOSS, ART OF HEALING', 1),
(85, 'CANADIAN IMMIGRATION LAWS FOR HEALTHCARE JOBS', 'canadian-immigration-laws-for-healthcare-jobs', '5bf3e0200c141.jpg', '2018-09-26', '<p><b>Work experience during the application process</b></p><p>Applicants will need to have at least one-year of consistent full time or part time experience&nbsp;in healthcare sectors in the last decade. According to the Canadian immigration laws, full-&nbsp;time work is calculated to be 37.5 hours per week of practice. They usually accept very short&nbsp;breaks in the continuity of employment. Applicants might be employed as the application&nbsp;process often tends to be lengthy and complicated. However, as long as the applicant presents&nbsp;valid documents, his or her experience between the point of applying and acceptance will be&nbsp;counted by the visa officer. Applicants should provide updated work documents at regular&nbsp;periods before submission for consideration during the assessment period.</p><p><b>Occupational caps</b></p><p>There are caps to any and every occupation in the country every year. Immigration, Refugee&nbsp;and Citizenship Canada (CIC) admit only admits a fixed number of individuals for&nbsp;professions on any given year. Presently, a total of about 5000 skilled workers’ applicants are&nbsp;processed every year and 300 per occupation. However, the caps do not consider applicants&nbsp;with arranged employment or PhD programs. As the caps in the healthcare industry are&nbsp;always in high demand, it is necessary to apply as soon as possible.</p><p><b>Validation of work documents</b></p><p>Applicants will need to prove the validity of their past work experience during application.&nbsp;Income tax returns and receipts are not enough to suffice the matter. The best option is to&nbsp;offer the letter of reference from the past or present employers. The document must have the&nbsp;signature of the official and that too, on the company letterhead. The message must feature&nbsp;the period of employment, salary, position, duties with the card of the individual himself.</p><p>If the applicants cannot provide these details, then they must include a detail explanation of&nbsp;the situation. Their next alternative will be to provide old contract documents with employers&nbsp;and performance appraisals. In case, this is also not possible, then the applicant’s situation&nbsp;might be in jeopardy. He or she will need to provide some documentation to the CIC that will&nbsp;prove his or her work experience in the past.</p><p><b>Language and the IELTS or TEF Exam</b></p><p>Each applicant- including those born and raised in English speaking countries must offer&nbsp;results of an IELTS exam along with the application. The only acceptable English language&nbsp;tests are the International English Language Testing System (IELTS). The review is&nbsp;conducted across the globe. Applicants will be unable to proceed further without submitting&nbsp;the results of this exam.</p><p><b>Adaptability</b></p><p>Applicants are judged on the merit of their adaptability prospect by the CIC. They are given&nbsp;an extra edge if they have previous experience in education or work in Canada. Having&nbsp;relatives and friends or arranged employment also counts in the case.</p><p>More Information please visit our website : <a href=\"#\" style=\"color:red;\">www.uhcstaffing.com</a></p><p><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b></b><br></p><p><b><br></b><br></p>', 'Occupational caps', 'CANADIAN IMMIGRATION LAWS FOR HEALTHCARE JOBS', 'UHC Staffing offers complete details about CANADIAN IMMIGRATION LAWS FOR HEALTHCARE JOBS.', 'CANADIAN IMMIGRATION LAWS, CANADIAN HEALTHCARE JOBS', 1),
(86, 'WHAT ARE COMPANIES LIKE AMAZON, BERKSHIRE HATHAWAY AND JP MORGAN CHASE DOING TO CHANGE HEALTHCARE', 'what-are-companies-like-amazon-berkshire-hathaway-and-jp-morgan-chase-doing-to-change-healthcare', '5bf3e84ea0a20.jpg', '2018-10-02', '<div>Healthcare is essential in any country due to the universal fact that people get injured or fall ill, and hospitals are necessary to identify and aid diverse kinds of ailments and diseases. The industry has an extraordinary power to transform lives. It helps millions and millions of people return to life daily. However, there is one big question that is standing in front of its growth today. What can transform healthcare in these modern times?</div><div><br></div><div><div>The leading or viable solution points towards big corporations and companies which act as employers in the global spectrum of the healthcare industry. They face a regular challenge of offering their workers with low-cost but high-quality care. The picture was somewhat similar back in the days of World War II when industrialist and shipbuilder Henry Kaiser transformed the healthcare for his employees. His idea was eventually turned into the Kaiser Permanente health plan. Drawing inspiration from this, big entities like Amazon and JP Morgan Chase are making their strides to introduce independent companies that will have free from profit-making incentives and constraints.</div><div><br></div><div><div>Expert minds are identifying three areas in healthcare that these companies are more likely to focus on.</div><div><ol><li>Amazon’s image has changed drastically since its inception, as the business has evolved into a creative collection and source of data to benefit consumers purchasing across the diverse range of products and services. The company has the knack of finding innovative ways to break the conventions of infrastructural complications. Companies like Amazon and Apple are trying to abolish the lack of standardisation to share data that had made it tough to unleash the raw and untapped potential of that data to feed analytics.</li><li>The insufficient presence of competition and pricing transparency between healthcare providers affects the insane high costing of healthcare. The companies are planning to implement techniques that determine their online marketplace to establish a national cost network of hospitals, pharmacies and physicians. The transparent cost network would enable the patients to get full coverage for the highest-value providers. However, they would have to pay more than usual.</li><li>The only area in healthcare that has been both tremendously criticised and scrutinised is pharmacy expenses. Companies like JP Morgan Chase and Berkshire Hathaway (Warrant Buffet) are adept at creating value-based contracting solutions to offer pharmaceutical manufacturers with the better predictable flow of profit. The data management and analytic capabilities of Amazon could monitor the improvement of medication adherence, evaluate the customised medicine prospects, and supervise medical outcomes. The information generated from this may contribute to bringing some change in the cost curve.</li></ol><p>More Information please visit our site <a href=\"#\"> www.uhcstaffing.com</a></p><p><br></p><p><br></p></div></div></div>', 'healthcare california', 'United healthcare Staffing Agency California', 'what are companies like amazon, berkshire hathaway and jp morgan chase doing to change healthcare', 'Healthcare Jobs in California', 1);

